act between middle-aged adults and their parents who live elsewhere differ in East Asian countries and the U.S.? How does female employment vary based on family factors and do these factors affect employment across societies?Policy makers and demographic and family researchers both in the U.S. and Asia will find this book a vital resource for understanding the dynamics of family life in contrasting modern societies. Contributors: Larry L. Bumpass, Yong-Chan Byun, Minja Kim Choe, Karen Oppenheim Mason, Ronald R. Rindfluss, Noriko O. Tsuya.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aFamiliesvCross-cultural studies. 0aFamilieszJapan. 0aFamilieszKorea (South). 0aFamilieszUnited States. 0aWork and familyvCross-cultural studies. 0aWork and familyzJapan. 0aWork and familyzKorea (South). 0aWork and familyzUnited States. 0aWork and family. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / Marriage & Long-Term Relationships.2bisacsh1 aBumpass, Larry L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBumpass, Larry L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aByun, Yong-Chan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoe, Minja Kim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMason, Karen Oppenheim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRindfuss, Ronald R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsuya, Noriko O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsuya, Noriko O., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUHP eBook Package 2000-2013z978311056414308iTitle is part of eBook pack